{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VCLSEb4SCVvvGAQvDRczQy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three jobs completed successfully. Here's the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Results\n\n### Bug Fixes Applied\n\n1. **AQE `skewedPartitionThresholdInBytes` misconfiguration** — The Python script in `skew-job-aqe.yaml` set this to `\"1b\"` (1 byte), causing Spark to treat *every* partition as skewed and split them all — massive overhead instead of improvement. Fixed to `\"256mb\"` (the Spark 3.x default).\n\n2. **Resource contention from concurrent execution** — The broadcast and AQE jobs ran simultaneously when first applied, competing for limited CPU (500m limit each). Re-ran them sequentially for accurate comparison.\n\n### Performance Comparison\n\n| Strategy | Elapsed | vs Baseline | Skew Ratio |\n|----------|---------|-------------|------------|\n| **baseline** (no optimization) | 17.6s | — | 44x |\n| **broadcast join** | 8.59s | **2.1x faster** | 44x (handled by broadcast) |\n| **AQE skew join** | 9.09s | **1.9x faster** | 44x (AQE splits hot partitions) |\n\n### How Each Strategy Works\n\n- **Baseline**: `repartition(20, \"product_id\")` creates severely skewed partitions (max 11,579 rows vs min 263). The sort-merge join stalls on the hot-product partitions.\n- **Broadcast join**: Broadcasts the small `products` table (100 rows) to all executors — eliminates the shuffle entirely, so skew in `orders` doesn't matter.\n- **AQE skew join**: Spark detects skewed partitions at runtime and auto-splits them, then reads matching build-side data multiple times to compensate. With `256mb` threshold (correctly sized for this dataset), no unnecessary splitting occurs and the skewed partitions are handled adaptively."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":170,"cache_read_input_tokens":69466,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":170},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c5ea2f5e-8848-4808-9ec7-307e9e282c27","uuid":"4a8ba4da-3cd5-4ee5-8816-17d38cbd99e3","request_id":"req_011Cc4sDH4XPbcwHY81BqfxT"}
